Class AbstractGcmService

java.lang.Object
  android.content.Context

              android.app.IntentService
                  com.jdroid.android.gcm.AbstractGcmService
All Implemented Interfaces:
android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2
public abstract class AbstractGcmService
extends android.app.IntentService

Base IntentService to handle Google Cloud Messaging (GCM) messages. You need to add the following permissions to your manifest: 

 <permission android:name="[app package].permission.C2D_MESSAGE" android:protectionLevel="signature" />
 <uses-permission android:name="[app package].permission.C2D_MESSAGE" />
 <uses-permission android:name="com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEIVE" />
 <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WAKE_LOCK" />
 <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS" />

Constructor Detail

AbstractGcmService

protected AbstractGcmService()
Constructor that does not set a sender id, useful when the sender id is context-specific.

When using this constructor, the subclass must override #getSenderIds(Context), otherwise methods such as onHandleIntent(Intent) will throw an IllegalStateException on runtime.
